---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="page-header">
				<h1>About T-Stories</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">Learning through immersive AI-generated storytelling</p>
			</section>
			
			<section class="mission">
				<div class="container">
					<div class="section-content">
						<h2>Our Mission</h2>
						<p>
							T-Stories is on a mission to transform how we learn new skills by harnessing 
							the power of storytelling and artificial intelligence. We believe that stories 
							are the most effective way to learn because they engage our emotions, provide 
							context, and make abstract concepts concrete and memorable.
						</p>
						<p>
							Our AI-generated long-form stories are crafted to teach real skills through 
							narrative-driven tutorials that mirror human experience. Whether you're learning 
							to code, design, write, or photograph, our stories place you in the shoes of 
							someone going through the learning journey, complete with challenges, setbacks, 
							and triumphs.
						</p>
						<blockquote>
							"Tell me a fact and I'll learn. Tell me a truth and I'll believe. But tell me a story and it will live in my heart forever."
							<footer>— Native American Proverb</footer>
						</blockquote>
					</div>
					<div class="section-image">
						<img src="/about-mission.html" alt="People learning together" loading="lazy" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			
			<section class="approach alt-section">
				<div class="container reverse">
					<div class="section-content">
						<h2>Our Approach</h2>
						<p>
							Each T-Stories tutorial is built on three key principles:
						</p>
						<ul class="principles">
							<li>
								<strong>Narrative Structure:</strong> Just as great novels have compelling characters and plot 
								arcs, our tutorials follow real-world learning journeys with challenges, obstacles, 
								and moments of breakthrough understanding.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Practical Application:</strong> We emphasize learning by doing. Our stories include 
								practical examples, code snippets, and exercises that can be applied immediately.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Context and Relevance:</strong> Rather than teaching isolated techniques, we show 
								how skills fit into broader workflows and real-world scenarios.
							</li>
						</ul>
						<p>
							By combining these elements with the capabilities of AI, we can create personalized, 
							engaging learning experiences that adapt to different skill levels and learning styles.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="section-image">
						<img src="/about-approach.html" alt="Our unique storytelling approach" loading="lazy" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			
			<section class="science">
				<div class="container">
					<div class="section-content">
						<h2>The Science Behind Storytelling</h2>
						<p>
							Our approach isn't just engaging—it's backed by cognitive science. When we learn 
							through stories, multiple areas of our brain activate simultaneously, creating 
							stronger neural connections than fact-based learning alone.
						</p>
						<div class="stats-grid">
							<div class="stat-card">
								<h3>22x</h3>
								<p>Stories can be up to 22 times more memorable than facts alone</p>
							</div>
							<div class="stat-card">
								<h3>65%</h3>
								<p>Higher retention rates when information is presented in narrative form</p>
							</div>
							<div class="stat-card">
								<h3>98%</h3>
								<p>Increase in emotional engagement when learning through storytelling</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<p>
							When we experience a story, our brains produce oxytocin, which enhances our 
							ability to empathize with the characters—in this case, someone on a learning 
							journey similar to yours. This creates an emotional connection that makes 
							the material more meaningful and therefore easier to retain.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="section-image">
						<img src="/about-science.html" alt="The science of storytelling" loading="lazy" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			
			<section class="team alt-section">
				<div class="container centered">
					<h2>The Team Behind T-Stories</h2>
					<p class="team-intro">
						We're a diverse team of educators, content creators, engineers, and AI specialists united 
						by our passion for transformative learning experiences. Together, we're developing new 
						ways to make skill acquisition more engaging, effective, and enjoyable.
					</p>
					
					<div class="cta-section">
						<h3>Join Us on This Journey</h3>
						<p>
							We're constantly improving our platform and adding new stories across different skills 
							and expertise levels. Explore our current collection, and check back often for new additions.
						</p>
						<div class="cta-buttons">
							<a href="/blog/" class="button primary">Explore Our Stories</a>
							<a href="/categories/" class="button secondary">Browse by Topic</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 100%;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.page-header {
		background-color: #f8f9fa;
		padding: 4rem 2rem;
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
	}

	.subtitle {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	section {
		padding: 4rem 2rem;
	}

	.alt-section {
		background-color: #f8f9fa;
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		display: flex;
		gap: 4rem;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.container.reverse {
		flex-direction: row-reverse;
	}

	.container.centered {
		flex-direction: column;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.section-content {
		flex: 1;
	}

	.section-image {
		flex: 1;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	.section-image img {
		max-width: 100%;
		height: auto;
		border-radius: 8px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	h3 {
		font-size: 1.8rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	p {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	blockquote {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-style: italic;
		padding: 1rem 2rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
		border-left: 5px solid var(--accent);
		background-color: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.5);
	}

	blockquote footer {
		font-size: 1rem;
		text-align: right;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		font-style: normal;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	.stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		margin: 3rem 0;
	}

	.stat-card {
		background-color: white;
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		text-align: center;
	}

	.stat-card h3 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		color: var(--accent);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.stat-card p {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1rem;
	}

	.principles {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
	}

	.principles li {
		padding: 0.75rem 0;
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 2rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.principles li:before {
		content: "→";
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: bold;
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		top: 0.75rem;
	}

	.team-intro {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto 4rem;
	}

	.cta-section {
		background-color: white;
		padding: 3rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		margin-top: 3rem;
		max-width: 800px;
		margin-left: auto;
		margin-right: auto;
	}

	.cta-buttons {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-weight: 600;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.button.primary {
		background-color: var(--accent);
		color: white;
	}

	.button.primary:hover {
		background-color: var(--accent-dark);
		transform: translateY(-3px);
	}

	.button.secondary {
		background-color: white;
		color: var(--accent);
		border: 2px solid var(--accent);
	}

	.button.secondary:hover {
		background-color: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.5);
		transform: translateY(-3px);
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.page-header h1 {
			font-size: 2.5rem;
		}

		.subtitle {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
		}

		.container {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 2rem;
		}

		.container.reverse {
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		.stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.cta-buttons {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 1rem;
		}
	}
</style>
